<section class="overview" id="2027">
  <h2>2027 — Northern Tier</h2>
  <p class="lead">7-Night Canoe Trek in Minnesota's Boundary Waters</p>

  <div class="stack-overview">
    <h3>Logistics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Fly:</strong> Atlanta (ATL) → Minneapolis (MSP)</li>
      <li><strong>Shuttle:</strong> MSP → Ely, MN</li>
      <li><strong>Duration:</strong> 7 nights</li>
      <li><strong>Focus:</strong> Paddling, portaging, teamwork</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Cost</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>$1,600–$2,100 per participant</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Training Plan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Monthly conditioning hikes:</strong> 3–5 miles</li>
    <li><strong>Canoe skills workshops:</strong> Strokes, maneuvering, capsize drills</li>
    <li><strong>Portage load training:</strong> Practice carrying loaded canoes</li>
    <li><strong>2-night canoe shakedown weekend:</strong> Local practice trip</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="overview" id="2028">
  <h2>2028 — Philmont Scout Ranch</h2>
  <p class="lead">12-Day Backpacking Trek through New Mexico's Sangre de Cristo Mountains</p>

  <div class="stack-overview">
    <h3>Logistics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Fly:</strong> Atlanta (ATL) → Albuquerque (ABQ)</li>
      <li><strong>Transport:</strong> Ground to base</li>
      <li><strong>Duration:</strong> 12 days</li>
      <li><strong>Focus:</strong> High elevation, endurance</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Cost</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>$3,000–$3,800 per participant</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Training Plan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Progressive hikes:</strong> Up to 10–12 miles</li>
    <li><strong>Pack training:</strong> Weights up to 45 lbs</li>
    <li><strong>2–3 backpacking shakedown weekends:</strong> Multi-night practice</li>
    <li><strong>Altitude education & bear procedures</strong></li>
  </ul>
</section>

